[07:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'plugin six. This is OpenAI\'s Codex plugin. This is kind of funny, right? OpenAI has their own Claude code plugin where you can integrate Codex directly into Claude code. It\'s kind of crazy at'

[08:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a high level to think about this, but it highlights something that you need to understand. Right now, you\'re operating inside Claude code\'s ecosystem. But Claude code, the interface you\'re using, is essentially just a way to interact with Claude\'s AI model. But the reality'

[08:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is you don\'t have to use Claude\'s AI model, and this is a way to use Claude code, but to reference a different model. This is a concept of multi-model, which is important to understand. And there are two reasons why multi-model is so important. The first is that'

[08:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'different models are better at different things. The same way you go to multiple doctors to get different opinions, if you\'re running into an issue, by using a different model, you might be able to solve it quickly or in a different way than the other model suggesting. The'

[08:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'second is that model independence is a muscle worth flexing. A lot of the models that you use right now are VC subsidized, which means that investors are essentially paying for tokens, knowing that they\'re going to lose money in the short term to get customers'

